[This dispute has some merit. Definitive governmental declarations should
be tempered by scientific knowledge. Nonetheless, such knowledge should be
available to people on both sides of the issue. It might be best to refer
to "black lake virus" as "Laguna Negra virus" because that is the name of
the virus in English as well as in Spanish. This virus has been isolated
in Paraguay and the vertebrate host there is _Calomys laucha_. The
vertebrate host of Andes virus is thought to be _Oligoryzomys
longicaudatus_. Chile is a long, narrow country and extends north/south
through many ecologic zones, so it may be that the vertebrate host of a
hantavirus in the north of Chile may be different from the vertebrate host
of a hantavirus in the south. As well, the viruses may be different. --Mod
CHC
